    "question_id" : 16137713,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Assuming the file is called \"CopyFile.java\", do the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>javac CopyFile.java\njava -cp . CopyFile\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The first line compiles the source code into executable byte code. The second line executes it, first adding the current directory to the class path (just in case).</p>\n"
