    "creation_date" : 1494562116,
    "answer_id" : 43929138,
    "question_id" : 16137713,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/EE25R.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/EE25R.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a>\nSTEP 1: FIRST OPEN THE COMMAND PROMPT WHERE YOUR FILE IS LOCATED. (right click while pressing shift)<br>\nSTEP 2: THEN USE THE FOLLOWING COMMANDS TO EXECUTE.\n        (lets say the file and class name to be executed is named as Student.java)The example program is in the picture background.</p>\n\n<pre><code>     javac Student.java\n     java Student\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/P2vTH.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/P2vTH.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11360616,
      "reputation" : 181,
      "user_id" : 8328871,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4c0bdf0c6593d1da9eeaa3356e56d85d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Horsey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8328871/horsey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1548576300,
    "creation_date" : 1548576300,
    "answer_id" : 54386200,
    "question_id" : 16137713,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As of Java 9, the JDK includes <code>jshell</code>, a Java REPL.</p>\n\n<p>Assuming the JDK 9+ <code>bin</code> directory is correctly added to your path, you will be able to simply:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Run <code>jshell File.java</code> — <code>File.java</code> being your file of course. </li>\n<li>A prompt will open, allowing you to call the <code>main</code> method: <code>jshell&gt; File.main(null)</code>.</li>\n<li>To close the prompt and end the JVM session, use <code>/exit</code></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Full documentation for JShell can be found <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/jshell/introduction-jshell.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
